bug.short_desc: Missing option to create encrypted logical volumes
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1269345 Screenshot
Description of problem: In classic manual partitioning it is possible to encrypt LVM logical volumes. This option is missing from blivet-gui.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): Fedora 26 Alpha
How reproducible: always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Use blivet-gui for partitioning. 2. On free space create LVM2 volume group. 3. Choose '+' to create device on volume group.
Actual results: The option to create encrypted logical volume is missing.
Expected results: Checkbox for encryption and edits for password are present.
Thanks for noticing, didn't know Anaconda can do that. Fixed.
